Family: tnum_correct_add

Asserts soundness of the BPF verifier's tnum (tristate-number)
addition: for any concretes x in tnum (av, am) and y in (bv, bm),
the value x+y lies in the tnum returned by tnum_add.

Tnum (v, m) of width n represents the set of x in [n] such that
x & ~m == v & ~m,
i.e. m records the unknown bits and v records the pinned-to-1 bits.

The add algorithm is the bit-level construction from Vishwanathan,
Harishankar, Bhat, Nagarakatte ('Sound, Precise, and Fast Abstract
Interpretation with Tristate Numbers', arXiv:2105.05398). It is used
inside the Linux kernel to track register values across BPF
instructions.

The k = 8 variant operates on k-bit tnums.
